Interpretation:

The 8x run showed the model can use H100s efficiently, but it did not close the
gap to the official baseline. The final export gap remained the binding issue:
train-time validation was much better than final exported BPB. The clearest
architecture improvement was prime-skip recurrent routing, which improved both
quality and speed while leaving substantial artifact headroom, but it was not
rerun on 8xH100 before the pod shut down.
